<h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Plugins</h1>

<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">
  Plugins extend botster with custom behavior. They're Lua scripts loaded at hub startup.
</p>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Plugin location</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-4">
  Place plugins in the <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">plugins/</code>
  directory at either level:
</p>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>~/.botster/plugins/my-plugin/init.lua        # Device-level (all repos)
your-repo/.botster/plugins/my-plugin/init.lua # Repo-level (this repo only)</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Plugin structure</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-4">
  Each plugin is a directory with an <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">init.lua</code> entry point:
</p>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>plugins/
  my-plugin/
    init.lua    # Entry point, loaded at startup</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Load order</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400">
  Plugins are loaded in alphabetical order. Device-level plugins load first, then repo-level.
  Repo plugins override device plugins with the same name.
  Plugins support hot reload &mdash; changes take effect without restarting the hub.
</p>
